programme.desc: A religious-themed newsmagazine, one of TV's longest-running programs. programme.desc: In 1973, U.S. businessman Ed Horman arrives in Chile to look for his son, Charles, a politically left-leaning journalist who disappeared during a military coup. Charles' wife, Beth, has been looking for some time, but her requests for help from the U.S. consulate have thus far produced few results. As Ed and Beth try to figure out what really happened to Charles, Ed realizes that the American officials may know more than they're telling(n).(n)

programme.title: Ouija
programme.desc: Following the sudden death of her best friend, Debbie, Laine finds an antique Ouija board in Debbie's room and tries to use it to say goodbye. He uses unorthodox methods to reach out to his students, who face enormous pressures from their parents and the school. With Keating's help, students Neil Perry, Todd Anderson and others learn to break out of their shells, pursue their dreams and seize the day(n).(n)

programme.title: Jackpot
programme.desc: Jackpot, Nevada is a town one hundred miles south of Twin Falls, Idaho. But ``Jackpot'' also means the payout of a slot machine-wealth without effort.
